Two issues I'm seeing here. Firstly, what exactly makes the network of tunnels anomalous? Right now, they're described but there's nothing that explicitly explains why they've been given an SCP designation in the first place. Secondly, I feel that the interview could stand to be tightened up a little, in terms of cutting the initial introductions/expositing to get straight to the riddle shenanigans. I'm not a fan of using interviews as an expository, so I initially got a little bored before the riddle part came up. Oh, also, the guy speaks modern English, so that breaks disbelief somewhat, though admittedly I'm not sure how 15th century English actually sounded like.







